metadata.name: On the sea, I ... #138
metadata.description:
Generative painting based on churning waves with floating buoys. Represented in three different media.

Features:
- Three drawing styles: "watercolor" 70%, "brush" 30%, or "block" 70%
- Warm white or blue waves
- Variable border and column sizes
- Number of columns
- Calm waves at the edges or center
- Color 80% or red 20% buoys
- Buoy drawing style, "watercolor" or "brush"

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 928x1200px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

Add '&size=#' to the end of the live view URL to render a variation of your edition at a resolution up to 3,000 px.

metadata.name: Extreme Ways #267
metadata.description:
« Extreme ways are back again
Extreme places I didn't know
I broke everything new again
Everything that I'd owned
I threw it out the windows, came along
Extreme ways I know move apart The colors of my sea
Perfect color me… »
Song/Lyrics by Moby

All pieces are broken again and again…

Controls
Extreme ways contains some interactivity if you wish to explore.
Since this artwork is complex it takes time to draw, be patient. 

Press h in live mode to list the possibilities and see tips for interactivity usage.
Key ’s’  : Save an image of the output at the current resolution
Key 1-9 : Change resolution
Key ‘c’ : Change colors
Key ‘m’ : Change main style
Key ‘d’ : Change drawing style
…
 

Pricing
Proposed as a Dutch Auction 11-9-7-5 tez with a step every 10 minutes.


Features
Main features are listed : Main style, drawing style, etc…
I do not think rarity will be a good indicator of the quality of the output.
Trust your taste and buy on the secondary what you like…
Lots of parameters are used internally to ensure a large variety in the outputs.

metadata.name: Atoms' Gaze #100
metadata.description:
How the lives of many affect the whole.

A holistic exploration of the growth of crystalline structures. Discovering the complexity of natural forms built from the simple rules of a deterministic system. What choice do individuals have but to be part of the story?

As microscopic particles interact and coalesce they form the macrocosm. The path they take however, is only known once it is complete. Along the way they may encounter many or none at all; each instance defining its past and future. The only knowns are that this will be the only path they take and that it'll always end.

Enjoy watching the structures form. Due to the nature of the system it may take some time to complete. Once it's fully rendered you can download a full resolution image by ***double clicking/tapping***

Features include: palette, foreground and background structures, particle rules, number of particles, colour displacement and noise.

Created on Chrome desktop 100.0 on 2022-04-16. Results on other browsers/devices may vary.

metadata.name: Sprocket Factory #256
metadata.description:
Just an ordinary scene from a typical day, working as a Sprocket Factory engineer. Inspiration for this work is drawn from the composable nature of blockchain smart contracts and the flow of value between networks of autonomous machines and free-willed individuals.

"A Doodle, Ringer, and Fidenza walk into a Space Bar..."

- Live renderer best viewed in Chrome.
- Press "P" to export an PNG raster image (10k resolution.)
- Press "S" to export an SVG vector.
